# Workshop Architecture

Build this app as a local-first Flutter expense tracker for beginner learners.

## Product Architecture

Use this mental model for every feature:

1. Rich client
   - Flutter UI, navigation, forms, local state, local SQLite, camera/photo picker, device OCR.
   - Core expense tracking must work without Supabase, Vercel, OpenRouter, or paid accounts.

2. Backend / cloud
   - Supabase is for auth, database, RLS, and cross-device sync.
   - Vercel serverless functions are for protecting secrets and calling AI providers.
   - Never put LLM API keys, service role keys, or paid-provider secrets in Flutter client code.

3. AI layer
   - AI features must be optional and demo-safe.
   - Use demo/mock mode first, then wire real APIs behind Vercel.
   - AI outputs should be structured and explainable when possible, for example category, confidence, reason.

4. Business model
   - Free must include useful basic local functionality.
   - Pro should unlock high-value or ongoing-cost capabilities: AI classification, AI monthly insights, cloud sync, higher quota.
   - Expensive VLM receipt recognition should be designed as credits or an add-on, not silently free.

## Teaching Constraints

- Prefer simple, readable code over clever abstractions.
- Explain changes in beginner-friendly language.
- Before large edits, list files you plan to change and why.
- Do not introduce new frameworks or cloud services unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve the Tier A path: local app + demo AI mode must keep working without external accounts.

